00:06:37.000 --> 00:06:44.000
And, you know, Anna's part kind of transitions into, you know, the next question is, for those of you who have attended,

00:06:44.000 --> 00:06:50.000
and this is not just for my co-hosts, but I think, you know, if anybody has anything they want to share on the community,

00:06:50.000 --> 00:06:55.000
what advice would you give to someone that's attending PositConf for the first time?

00:06:55.000 --> 00:06:57.000
Face yourself.

00:06:58.000 --> 00:07:06.000
Our goal on the program committee is to make sure that even if you're at conf, you feel FOMO,

00:07:06.000 --> 00:07:12.000
because there's, like, always at least one other talk you wish you could be listening to at the same time as this talk.

00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:16.000
So, you know, like, don't try and see everything.

00:07:16.000 --> 00:07:17.000
Don't try and do everything.

00:07:17.000 --> 00:07:23.000
All the talks will be available online pretty much as soon as we can after conf,

00:07:23.000 --> 00:07:28.000
so you can definitely catch anything you missed afterwards.

00:07:28.000 --> 00:07:31.000
And I know a few other people mentioned this in the chat, too.

00:07:31.000 --> 00:07:38.000
Like, it's quite nice to actually be able to attend conf virtually, even if you're there in person.

00:07:38.000 --> 00:07:46.000
If you need to get away from people for a bit, you can just go up to your hotel room and watch videos from the comfort of your bed.

00:07:46.000 --> 00:07:52.000
So that's one of my tips.

00:07:52.000 --> 00:08:00.000
