00:17:01.000 --> 00:17:20.000
I think we did, I think also, I mean, there's also Level Up Shiny for, Level Up with Shiny for R, which is kind of similar, not quite as advanced, but I think it includes quite a lot of the, like, some of the content from the previous Advanced R ones, too.

00:17:21.000 --> 00:17:38.000
Yeah, I think that makes sense. You know, obviously, Shiny for R has been around well over a decade, if I'm not mistaken. Shiny for Python is a little newer, so we're spending a little bit more time getting the word out for Shiny for Python.

00:17:38.000 --> 00:17:48.000
But, of course, both have, are under active development at Posit, and so it's not really one or the other, but really, you know, which language you prefer, or, you know, what you might be doing.

00:17:48.000 --> 00:18:04.000
